6TH GRADE ORIENTATION UPDATE
The 6th Grade Team is very sorry that we could not have you here in person for the 6th Grade Orientation, as we are so eager to meet each of you and welcome you to the Woodbury Junior High Family.

However, we worked very hard to make sure that we created a virtual experience that will give you all of the information you need to get you off to a great start in 6th grade, as well as an opportunity to meet your teachers before the first day of school.

Click on the link below and follow the presentation, which offers welcome videos, tutorials on how to access important sites, as well as access to the 6th grade website which will be used all year, and important dates leading up to the first day of school.

Please remember, we are here to help you throughout this entire process, so please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions.

https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1XQKtMAldXmnWAddtVKd-O-tFmDq-OThG8r_r9IalFgM/edit?usp=sharing

ATTENTION WOODBURY COMMUNITY
Ms. Wendy Romano will be retiring this year and has been a foundation of Walnut Street School the past several decades. Sadly, the Walnut school community will not be able to give her a traditional send off due to social distancing guidelines. However, our community has the opportunity to celebrate her virtually. If you ever had Ms. Romano as a teacher, whether you are still in school or currently an adult, and you still feel her impact on your life, please click the link below. Every comment on her LifeChanger profile counts as a vote. Let her know what impact she made in your life. Please share this link as well on social media. Thank you for showing your support for Ms. Wendy Romano! #LCOY

http://app.lifechangeroftheyear.com/nomination_detail.cfm?NominationID=5343&NominationYear=2020&fbclid=IwAR1CoVtUKmNJbsQF0Z6iAGDlv_XaXbqMImDRUJ0XnByJYZy4Ub3QtzgWp8g

We can use volunteers. If you are interested in volunteering, please reach out to vmyers@woodburysch.com

post_text:
SCHOOL PARADE UPDATE
After consulting with various community partners and reviewing current COVID-19 State quarantine guidelines, we have decided to deviate from our original plan to host a physical elementary wide teacher parade on Tuesday, April 14th. We have decided to err on the utmost side of safety for our students, staff and the broader Woodbury community. We are committed, however, to maintain a connection with our students, families and staff at this time. As a result, we will be modifying our original plan and holding an Elementary wide VIRTUAL school spirit week from Tuesday April 14th – Friday April 17th. We believe this will allow us to connect with our Woodbury families and create multiple opportunities to celebrate each other in a way that maintains the safety of all. A schedule for the VIRTUAL school spirit week will be posted here on the district Facebook page on Monday. Thank you for your understanding and support!
text:
SCHOOL PARADE UPDATE
After consulting with various community partners and reviewing current COVID-19 State quarantine guidelines, we have decided to deviate from our original plan to host a physical elementary wide teacher parade on Tuesday, April 14th. We have decided to err on the utmost side of safety for our students, staff and the broader Woodbury community. We are committed, however, to maintain a connection with our students, families and staff at this time. As a result, we will be modifying our original plan and holding an Elementary wide VIRTUAL school spirit week from Tuesday April 14th – Friday April 17th. We believe this will allow us to connect with our Woodbury families and create multiple opportunities to celebrate each other in a way that maintains the safety of all. A schedule for the VIRTUAL school spirit week will be posted here on the district Facebook page on Monday. Thank you for your understanding and support!

post_text:
ATTENTION WOODBURY FAMILIES
If you have 3, 4, or 5 year-olds at home, please take a moment to read these flyers (available in English and Spanish) for our Preschool and Kindergarten registration. You can enroll your child online using the directions below:

ONLINE REGISTRATION PROCESS
1. Go to Woodbury School District page: www.woodburysch.com
2. Click on the “About Us” tab
3. Click on “Registration Information” tab
4. Click on Online Registration (English) register with a username and email and then begin the online application.

PROCESO DE INSCRIPCIÓN EN LÍNEA
1.Vaya a la página del Distrito Escolar de Woodbury:
www.woodburysch.com
2. Haga clic en la pestaña "Acerca de nosotros"
3. Haga clic en la pestaña "Información de registro"
4. Haga clic en Registro en línea (inglés), regístrese con un nombre de usuario y correo electrónico y luego comience la solicitud en línea.

ATTENTION ALL WOODBURY FAMILIES
Tomorrow there will be two food service programs running simultaneously.

THE FOOD BANK OF SOUTH JERSEY
This program will run from 9:00AM - 11:00AM outside of the Gold Cafeteria at the Woodbury Junior-Senior HS. In the case of rain, the program will be moved into the Gold Cafeteria. Please do not arrive before 9:00AM as we will be finishing setting everything up.

WOODBURY CITY PUBLIC SCHOOLS
The district’s food service program will be running out of the Cap Paine Gymnasium lobby tomorrow from 9:00AM - 12:00PM. Families will be provided with 3 days worth of food for each child. Please note this pick-up is for families who didn’t pick up last Friday.

Please note that families may attend BOTH food service programs tomorrow.

Thank you to all of our Woodbury team members who have volunteered to help run and support the programs!

#WoodburyPride #GreatHappensHere #ItTakesAVillage

post_text: BEDTIME STORIES FROM THE WOO will start on Monday, March 16th at 7:00 PM. Woodbury staff members are signing up to read their favorite bedtime stories to all of the children in Woodbury from Monday through Friday while the district is closed. There will be three books read each night. The first two will be in English and the final book will be read in Spanish. Each night the "special guests" will show up here on our district FACEBOOK page at 7:00 PM, 7:15 PM, and 7:30 PM to read their favorite bedtime stories LIVE! We hope you and your children enjoy the experience! #WoodburyPride #GreatHappensHere #ItTakesAVillage

post_text: In the fall, Walnut School Resource officer, Mike McGee, noticed a lot of our students riding bikes and scooters to school. Unfortunately, many of our students weren't wearing a helmet. As a result, Officer Mike took it upon himself to reach out to our local American Legion with a proposal to raise enough to purchase a helmet for EVERY student in Walnut Street School & they were more than generous enough to support his cause. He spent time with the students getting proper measurements to ensure everyone is safe, and applying a reflective sticker to each helmet with the American Legion logo. Today officer Mike invited Kevin Mitchell from the American Legion and some other Woodbury Police Department Officers in to present the kids with their helmets and some bike safety information. #WoodburyPride #GreatHappensHere

post_text:
On February 10, 2020, Omicron Omicron Zeta Chapter hosted Lifting Words Off the Pages an African-American Read-In at Evergreen Avenue Elementary School in Woodbury, New Jersey. The Zetas and Amicae along with other community partners read a book to a class, solicited questions and conducted activities that lifted the words off the pages. The readers also shared with the students their chosen career, emphasizing the importance of reading and its impact on their lives.

This program is a part of the National African American Read-In, which is the nation’s first and oldest event dedicated to diversity in literature. It was established in 1990 by the Black Caucus of the National Council of Teachers of English to make literacy a significant part of Black History Month.
#WoodburyPride #GreatHappensHere

We recently held our official ribbon cutting for our monthly Food Pantry. Woodbury City Public Schools have partnered with Inspira Health and the Food Bank of South Jersey to provide food and other items to our families in need. In our first five months of operation, we have distributed items to almost 300 families, representing almost 900 Woodbury residents. Our next Food Pantry will take place on Wednesday, February 26. #WoodburyPride
#GreatHappensHere

APP.LIFECHANGEROFTHEYEAR.COM
Crystal Ramirez

LifeChanger of the Year
December 9, 2019 at 5:00 PM ·

Recently, Woodbury City Public Schools has experienced a large influx of students enrolling from Latin America. Many of these students are coming over to the United States without their parents or family, and they are in desperate need of assistance. Enter Crystal Ramirez, a bilingual educator from Evergreen Avenue Elementary School. She's passionate about making sure these students have the resources and services they need to succeed. Her work has literally saved so many lives, and she has brought so much comfort to these students, from being a simple shoulder to cry on to being a maternal figure who can offer advice. We're thankful for LifeChangers like her!

post_text: For the fifth consecutive year, the Road Runners Club of Woodbury (RRCW) graciously donated dozens of jackets to the Woodbury City Public Schools. A portion of the race entry fee from Hot Run in the Summertime (http://www.rrcwoodbury.com/rrcw-race-series/hot-run-in-the-summertime/ ) is set aside to provide local children new jackets just in time for the winter months. RRCW partners with Operation Warm to provide this wonderful donation. The Woodbury City Public Schools is appreciative for the efforts of the RRCW and looks forward to a continued partnership in future years.

ATTENTION EDUCATORS that are still looking for a position....

We are conducting interviews this week for a preschool and 1st grade instructional assistant. We need two amazing individuals to serve as the "2nd teacher" in the classroom. We were blessed this year with phenomenal professionals who recently received full-time jobs. The two positions are an awesome opportunity to get your foot in the door, gain amazing experience, and receive top notch training without many of the responsibilities of a full-time teacher. We may be a bit biased, but we believe we have the BEST STAFF TO WORK WITH AND BEST SCHOOLS TO WORK AT IN ALL OF SOUTH JERSEY! All candidates must possess NJ Teacher Certification. The positions are part-time and pay $16.70/hr for 29 hours/wk. Please send your resumes ASAP to BOTH kagresta@woodburysch.com and tbraddock@woodburysch.com. Thank you for your time and support!

post_text:
Congratulations to Mr. Tom Braddock for being selected to receive the NAACP Gloucester County 2019 Most Prestigious President’s Award. He is being recognized for clearly demonstrating his commitment to our school community through his gift of time and talent that he so generously gives to others.

Mr. Braddock will be recognized as a community “Game Changer” at the NAACP’s annual signature event, “the Gloucester County NAACP Black & White Gala”, on Sunday, November 3, 2019, at Auletto Caterers, Cooper Road, Deptford, NJ. Doors will open at 5:00 PM. The evening will include a social hour, dinner, entertainment, dancing, and the prestigious award presentation. If you would like to purchase tickets to attend the event and join in the celebration for Mr. Braddock, you can purchase tickets online at www.gloucestercountynaacp.org. #WoodburyPride

post_text: What a great day at Woodbury City Public Schools as we opened the 2019-2020 school year! Our school leaders and staff did an awesome job preparing for day one to be a great success and they pulled it off without a hitch. Our Superintendent, Andrew Bell, spent the entire day visiting each school. He started his morning at the Junior-Senior High School meeting and greeting students. He moved onto Evergreen Avenue Elementary and then made stops at West End Memorial and Walnut Street School. Thank you Superintendent Bell for coming out to support students, staff and parents! #WoodburyPride

EXCITING NEWS!
The Franklin Covey (Leader In Me) company will be coming to Woodbury on August 22nd to deliver a workshop called “The 7 Habits of Highly Effective Families”. The workshop is open to all of the adult members of our school community (parents, staff, and community members), but there are only 50 participant slots for this first event. The workshop is being held in the library over at Evergreen Avenue Elementary School from 8:30 AM – 4:30 PM. Please take a moment to review the attached pictures of the flyer. If you would like to attend the workshop please email Mr. Tom Braddock directly at tbraddock@woodburysch.com. Participation in the event will be on a first come first serve basis. #WoodburyPride #7Habits #LeaderInMe

post_text: Congratulations to Principal Tom Braddock! He is one of five educators in the state who have been selected to deliver a TedTalk at the NJDOE Statewide Equity Conference on July 31, 2019 at The College of New Jersey. Mr. Braddock’s talk is entitled, “You Can’t Teach ‘Em Until You Reach ‘Em”. The talk will highlight the impact the Standout Leader of the Week program and home visits have made on the Evergreen Avenue school community, and some of the other great work he and the Evergreen staff have done together over the last three years.

post_text: "Alyssa's Law" (A764) requires all NJ public schools to install silent panic alarms that will alert law enforcement during emergencies. The NJ Schools Development Authority is tasked with funding and managing the installation of the silent panic alarms in partnership with the NJ Department of Education. The NJDOE seeks feedback, comments and concerns from the public on school security and the school security bond. Please review the "Securing Our Children's Future" Bond Act Fact Sheet http://ow.ly/Bpy150uAFtq and complete the online survey by 6/18/19 https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/CR25ZVB For further information, please email futurebondact@doe.nj.gov
